Annotation

Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us
The patient shows elevated creatinine, low total CO₂, and significant proteinuria, suggesting impaired renal function with possible metabolic acidosis. Urine findings (cloudy, brown, low specific gravity, ketonuria, proteinuria, glucosuria) indicate possible renal tubular dysfunction or acute kidney injury. Low HbA1c with normal glucose may reflect recent changes or anemia. Recommend urgent clinical correlation and nephrology evaluation.
